The paper discusses federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). It also addresses privacy concerns and the use of differential privacy, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper proposes techniques for local adaptation of federated models, which involves multi-task learning and knowledge distillation, both of which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves analyzing data that is unbalanced and non-iid, which falls under the category of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits and drawbacks of federated learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
